<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<style>
  body { font-family: Calibri, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #1a1a1a; }
  h2 { color: #003366; border-bottom: 2px solid #003366; padding-bottom: 4px; }
  h3 { color: #005099; margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .impact { font-size: 1.05em; }
  .levers { margin-top: 8px; padding-left: 18px; }
  .levers li { margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .streak { color: #c0392b; font-weight: bold; }
  .footer { margin-top: 32px; font-size: 12px; color: #888; border-top: 1px solid #ddd; padding-top: 8px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h2>{{ subject }}</h2>
<p>Week of <strong>{{ digest.period_start }}</strong></p>

{% for m in digest.machines %}
<h3>{{ m.plant_wc }} — {{ m.department }}</h3>
<p class="impact">
  <strong>{{ m.plant_wc }}</strong> lost
  <strong>{{ "%.1f" | format(m.total_oee_impact) }} hours</strong> of OEE Impact this week
  {%- if m.outcome_1 %},
  driven primarily by <strong>{{ m.outcome_1 }}</strong>
  ({{ "%.1f" | format(m.outcome_1_hours) }} hrs)
  {%- if m.outcome_2 %} and <strong>{{ m.outcome_2 }}</strong>
  ({{ "%.1f" | format(m.outcome_2_hours) }} hrs){% endif %}{% endif %}.
</p>

{% if m.levers %}
<p>To close those gaps, focus on these top levers:</p>
<ul class="levers">
{% for l in m.levers %}
  <li>
    <strong>{{ l.name }}{% if l.reasons %} — {{ l.reasons }}{% endif %}</strong>
    ({{ l.parent_outcome }},
     {{ "%.1f" | format(l.hours) }} hrs lost,
     gap {{ "%.1f" | format(l.gap_pct * 100) }}%
     {%- if l.streak > 0 %},
     <span class="streak">{{ l.streak }}/4 weeks above BSP</span>{% endif %})
  </li>
{% endfor %}
</ul>
<p>
  Improving their gap and breaking their streak will move
  <strong>{{ m.outcome_1 }}{% if m.outcome_2 %} and {{ m.outcome_2 }}{% endif %}</strong>.
</p>
{% endif %}

{% endfor %}

<div class="footer">
  Generated automatically by the Folding Carton Actionable Intelligence Platform.
  Do not reply to this email.
</div>
</body>
</html>
